34. As I mentioned above (Room 20), kobolds are \u8220\'1cfailed\u8221\'1d dwarves. I thought I was pretty clever in coming up with this origin. The problem with it was twofold. According to the rules I created for the creation of dwarven \u8220\'1csons,\u8221\'1d a failed roll wasn't very likely. Even if it had been, I also established that, by custom, dwarves were limited to a single attempt at reproducing themselves, regardless of whether the attempt succeeded or not. Sure, some dwarves might buck that custom, but, even so, I had placed a cap on how many failed dwarves there likely to be are out there and it wasn't enough to explain why there were so many kobolds.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af7\afs24\alang1081\cf0\loch\f3\fs24\lang4105\rtlch \ltrch\loch

