35. I noted earlier (Room 1) that I contemplated having a monotheistic cosmology for the campaign setting. I never completely abandoned this idea\u8212\'14and in fact \u8220\'1ccheated,\u8221\'1d as I'll explain later\u8212\'14which is why there often relics of saints and holy men to be found in Dwimmermount. I'm quite fascinated by such objects and their veneration, so it only seemed right to include them. This particular relic is based on one I'd created earlier and which appeared in a small dungeon I wrote for the premier issue of the Fight On! fanzine (Spring 2008). That dungeon was one of the very first things I wrote after coming back to the D&D of my youth.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052\dbch\af7\afs24\alang1081\cf0\loch\f3\fs24\lang4105\rtlch \ltrch\loch

