49. I like unexplained\u8212\'14indeed unexplainable\u8212\'14events and effects. The temporal stasis effect in this room is something I simply thought would pique players' imaginations. I had no idea why it was operating when I keyed this room and still don't. I'm not really sure it matters, though if my players had taken a keen interest in it or started to theorize as to its origins, I might have given it some further thought. That's the way I do a lot of things as a referee: I come up with some vaguely defined notion and let the players loose on it. If it grabs their attention and they want to know more, I run with it; if they don't, I don't bother.}
