68. As I pondered the wider world beyond Dwimmermount, I found myself in a quandary. I liked most of the monsters and races of classical D&D, but I nevertheless felt there were too many of them. Including them all without some sense of how they fit into the larger cosmology was a non-starter for me. Even if the players and their characters never knew any of this stuff, I wanted to know it. I felt it was important to being able to present a believable fantasy world. That's how I came up with the idea of beast men (see Room 3), for example.}
